	     John H.  Tyson
	     
	  



executive



		John H. Tyson, American food products executive. Named Man of Year, Arkansas Poultry Industry, 1994. Board directors Area United Way; supporter Farm Aid; volunteer activities for well-being and education of Arkansas children; Member of Arkansas Poultry Federation  (past president), American Meat Institute, National Association Manufacturers.
		
       		



Background




Tyson, John H. was born on September 5, 1953 in Springdale, Arkansas, United States. Son of Don and Jean Tyson.
					
					



Education


	 		
			

			Bachelor of Business Administration, Southern Methodist University, 1975.
			
       			












Career


	 		
			Complex manager North Carolina area Tyson Foods, Inc., Springdale, Arkansas, vice president marketing corporation accounts, purchasing manager, retail sales manager Northeast states, president beef and pork division. President, chairman Tyson Foods Inc., 1998-1900, president, chairman, Chief Executive Officer, 2000—2001, chairman, Chief Executive Officer, 2001—2006, chairman, since 2006. Political liaison to Washington and Little Rock Tyson Foods, Inc.
			
       			












Membership


			Board directors Area United Way. Supporter Farm Aid; volunteer activities for well-being and education of Arkansas children. Member of Arkansas Poultry Federation  (past president), American Meat Institute, National Association Manufacturers.
			
    			







Personality

Interests

					Deep sea fishing, music, golf.
					
    			



Connections


			Married Kimberly McCoy. Children: John Randal, Olivia Laine.
			
    			








